<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{y}={13}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{8}{y}={36}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({1},{5}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --4. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{4}}{{8}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{4}}}{{8}}{\left({8}{x}+{1}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{4}}}{{8}}{\left({13}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{4}\right)}{x}+{0.5}{y}={6.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{8}{y}={36}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8.5}{y}={42.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{42.5}}{{8.5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={5}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{1}{\left({5}\right)}={13}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{\left({5}\right)}={13}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={13}-{\left({5}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{8}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={1}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({1},{5}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

